6 An Act relating to firearms; amending 20 O.S. 2021,
Section 129, which relates to the authority of judges
7 to carry firearms; extending authority to carry
firearms to retired municipal judges; providing an
8 exemption; authorizing the issuance of certain
written orders; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 20 O.S. 2021, Section 129, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 129. A. A judge of the district court, municipal
15 judge, or retired judge of the district court who receives a
16 statement from the appropriate retirement system verifying the
17 status of the person as a retired judge of the district court may
18 carry a firearm on his or her person anywhere in throughout the
19 state to use only for personal protection if the person has
20 successfully completed a handgun qualification course for court
21 officials developed by the Council on Law Enforcement Education and
22 Training. The Council on Law Enforcement Education and Training may
23 provide for an identification card to be issued to the judge of the
24 district court, retired judge of the district court, or municipal
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3062 Page 1

1 judg e and may provide application forms. If the person issued an
2 identification card is no longer eligible, that person shall
3 immediately return the identification card to the Council on Law
4 Enforcement Education and Training.
5 B. In addition to the requirements provided for in subsection A
6 of this section, a retired municipal judge, having served as a
7 municipal judge for twenty (20) cumulative years, as certified by
8 the Oklahoma Municipal Judges Association, and who is qualified to
9 serve as a municipal judge, may carry a firearm on his or her person
10 throughout the state to use only for personal protection; provided,
11 however, the retired municipal judge shall not be authorized to
12 carry the firearm into any district court of this state. Retired
13 district judges, district attorneys or assistant district attorneys
14 who are currently authorized to carry firearms throughout the state
15 pursuant to state law shall be exempt from the provisions of this
16 subsection.
17 C. The chief judge of the district court may issue a written
18 order allowing a municipal judge to carry a firearm within the
19 district court during the time period in which he or she serves as
20 the chief judge.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
